[5] Cholera - Uganda (Western Districts)
Date: Sat 14 Apr 2018
Source: The Independent [edited]
https://www.independent.co.ug/this-week-cholera-hits-hoima-kagadi/


For 2 months now, cholera has hit residents of Hoima, Kagadi and Kyegegwa including the refugee settlements. The number of people affected with the disease in Hoima has reached 2000 and an estimated 40 killed, while in Kyegegwa, about 300 cases and 22 deaths have been reported.

In Kagadi, James Olowo, the district health officer told media that over 20 cases had been reported by early April 2018 at Kitebere landing site on the shores of Lake Albert, but the number is expected to go up. Some of the samples have been taken to the Government Analytical Laboratory in Wandegeya, Kampala.

Olowo revealed that the district had constituted a team comprising 2 senior clinical officers with vast experience in infection control and management, a district disease surveillance focal person, lab technicians, and a Uganda Red Cross Society emergence response team.

