[7] Cholera - Nigeria (Yobe State)
Date: Wed 4 Apr 2018
Source: Daily Trust [edited]
https://www.dailytrust.com.ng/yobe-cholera-outbreak-death-toll-hits-13.html


13 persons have been confirmed dead in 160 reported cases as cholera continues to ravage Gashua town in Bade local government area of Yobe state. Daily Trust reported on Saturday, 31 Mar 2018, that the victims were admitted at the hospital's isolation center, where 6 people died out of the 62 cases recorded. However, a laboratory test on 10 patient samples found 8 positive, ending doubts about whether the outbreak could be gastroenteritis.

Mr Hassan Gadaka, the head of Records and Statistics of the hospital told our correspondent that more deaths had been recorded, increasing the number to 13. "From our records now, we have 13 deaths out of the 160 cholera patients hospitalized. Among the dead was a child from the 18 children under the age of 5 admitted in the hospital.

He said the patients were brought from 7 affected wards in Gashua town and one in Yusufari local government area: Sabo Gari, Lawan Musa, Katuzu, Lawan fannami, Zango, Sarkin hausawa, and kachallari in Yusufari.

[Byline: Hamisu Kabir Matazu]

